research_municipality_step.notes: Taylor, TX operates under a council-manager form of government. The City Council consists of five members: four from single-member districts and one at-large. The Mayor and Mayor Pro Tem are currently elected by the council from among its members for a one-year term. In May 2024, voters approved an amendment to the City Charter to change the at-large council position to Mayor, effective May 2026. Dwayne Ariola currently serves as both Mayor and the At-Large Council Member. Kelly Cmerek serves as both Mayor Pro Tem and the Council Member for District 3.
